page.title: 17Small Creatures at Stonegate
page.content: We went for a walk on a Wednesday in June looking for insects and minibeasts.As we were walking we saw some butterflies,including a small tortoiseshell and two wood butterflies.We found many flies,one of which was a green-bottle.We found lots of spiders;one of them had eggs and was very neatly wrapped up in a tight coccoon,protecting it from any enemies. Here are some of the other creatures we saw: ants,including a flying ant two bees a hoverfly mosquitoes an earwig and a baby earwig two beetles two moths a woodlouse.
